{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":667,"record_hash":"sha256:cd46028e757bc70b4cdb90b9d28f2c1bc89747ec1e9cc4f04466ef94b166c5f5","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:06:57.120Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Ran five read-only adversarial passes against [agent-trail.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md>). No edits made.\\n\\nStrongest verdict: **the spec is buildable, but still leaves room to ship a polished transcript dump that feels authoritative when it should feel evidential.**\\n\\nHigh-signal doc improvements:\\n\\n1. **Add a First-Minute Reviewer Contract**\\n   Reviewer must immediately know: match strength, what the human asked, what the agent claimed, validation status, evidence links, what is missing, and what the page does not prove.\\n\\n2. **Move technical facts out of the first screen**\\n   OIDs, cache status, `refs/meta/main`, public/read projections, etc. belong in “Technical details.” Primary UI should say things like “Matched by PR,” “Matched by branch,” “Captured metadata found.”\\n\\n3. **Replace “strength” with evidence tiers**\\n   Use clear tiers: `Direct`, `Supporting`, `Possible`, `Weak`. Avoid confidence-score vibes.\\n\\n4. **Quarantine branch-only matches**\\n   Do not auto-select branch-only sessions. Put them in a collapsed “Possible branch-related sessions” section with blunt copy: branch match is not PR-specific evidence.\\n\\n5. **Require source anchors**\\n   Every overview claim, warning, validation item, touched area, and open question must link to exact redacted source records. No uncited generated summary text in v1.\\n\\n6. **Separate agent claims from tool evidence**\\n   Use “Agent claimed,” not “Claim.” Validation must be outcome-specific: `Passed`, `Failed`, `Attempted`, `Skipped`, `Unknown`, with command/exit status when available.\\n\\n7. **Add negative evidence**\\n   Overview should say what was not found: no review-target match, no tests, no raw records, stale metadata, broad multi-topic session, branch-only evidence, etc.\\n\\n8. **Define the browsing path**\\n   Add a default journey:\\n   `PR overview -> why these sessions matched -> top evidence timeline -> expand claim/tool/test -> back to overview`.\\n   Also ban chronological transcript walls as the default page.\\n\\n9. **Make failure states actionable**\\n   Replace the bullet list with a state matrix: title, plain-language cause, what was checked, what was not checked, CTA, retry behavior, diagnostics. Copy must avoid implying “no agent work” unless proven.\\n\\n10. **Add loading/stale snapshot UX**\\n   On-demand generation can be slow. Define loading, timeout, retry, stale cached snapshot, refresh failure, and rate-limit behavior.\\n\\n11. **Add copy constraints**\\n   Ban reviewer-facing terms like “authored,” “proved,” “verified,” “guaranteed,” “complete history,” “audit,” “source of truth.” This product should sound useful, not magical or legalistic.\\n\\n12. **Say v1 does not compare claims to the PR diff**\\n   “Agent said it changed X” does not mean the PR contains X. Make that explicit.\\n\\nNo new product questions are blocking. My pick: patch the doc with these before building; especially `First-Minute Reviewer Contract`, `Evidence Contract`, `Weak Match UX`, and `Failure State Matrix`.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:06:57.120Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}